  "prompt": "How is Iphone 6s better than 6?",
  "response": "The iPhone 6s offers several improvements over the iPhone 6. Here are some of the key enhancements:\n\n1. **3D Touch**: The iPhone 6s introduced 3D Touch technology, which allows users to press firmly on the screen to access additional features and shortcuts, enabling a new way to interact with apps and content.\n\n2. **Improved Camera**: The rear camera on the iPhone 6s is 12 megapixels compared to the 8 megapixels on the iPhone 6. This means better image quality, improved low-light performance, and the ability to capture 4K video. The front camera was also upgraded to 5 megapixels for better selfies and supports features like Retina Flash for low-light conditions.\n\n3. **Enhanced Performance**: The iPhone 6s features the A9 chip, which is more powerful and efficient than the A8 chip found in the iPhone 6. This results in better performance, faster app launch times, and improved graphics performance for gaming and other applications.\n\n4. **Increased RAM**: The iPhone 6s has 2GB of RAM, doubling the 1GB found in the iPhone 6. This helps with multitasking and allows more apps to run smoothly in the background.\n\n5. **Stronger Build**: The iPhone 6s uses a stronger aluminum alloy (7000 series) for its chassis, making it less prone to bending compared to the iPhone 6.\n\n6. **Live Photos**: The iPhone 6s introduced Live Photos, which captures a few seconds of video along with your still pictures, adding a dynamic element to your photo library.\n\n7. **Faster Touch ID**: The Touch ID fingerprint sensor on the iPhone 6s is faster than that of the iPhone 6, providing quicker access to the device and apps that support biometric authentication.\n\nOverall, the iPhone 6s brought notable upgrades in terms of performance, camera capabilities, and new interactive features compared to the iPhone 6.",
